I’m sitting in my car with two sleeping kids watching it snow. I may just be romanticizing my own life but it feels like a movie. As my mind wanders i just keep coming back to the idea of belonging. I’m struck by this deep sense that we belong to each other. Being a parent can feel so heavy. The weight of this responsibility can crush you if you let it. But instead i like to let it fuel me. This responsibility inspires and encourages me to be my best self for these beautiful humans who call me mom. What an honor it is to belong to them. What a privilege it is to carry them in my heart at all times. What a gift it is to be forever linked to them. I’m so so proud of them and truly love that they are mine and i am theirs.

Penny Peace! We are obsessed with you! We thought our family was done growing but the moment that condom broke we knew you were chasing us down! (Thanks #trojan!!!) My heart was shattered in the months leading up to his birth. Easily the lowest point in my life. Once River arrived i was still deeply hurting and i honestly struggled to connect with him at in my most honest moments i questioned if we made a mistake having another baby. But in the most pure and perfect way this extravagant soul helped to put my hurting heart back together. We named him River Gold as a declaration of who he was even before he was growing in my womb. Only time would tell the story of how true his name would be. Now i look at him and explode with thankfulness over the gift of his life. He truly is our golden boy and one of my most beautiful treasures. If you’re in a hard season i just want to encourage you and say that as long as you keep going it will undoubtably get better. Your gold is on the way and i promise you it will be even more beautiful than you can imagine!

Things I’ve learned in 2023
1. Leaning in is the fastest way to peace. 
2. The world continues to spin no matter what is going on in your internal world- allow that to shift your perspective and bring you comfort instead of upsetting you. 
3. Prioritizing your health is wise and beautiful but being obsessed with self care is silly
4. Life is not slowing down, our kids are not getting any younger- and neither are we! So be present now because this work is holy! 
5. It’s also okay to take an extra long shower or hide out in the bathroom when necessary. There’s no prize for never taking a break! 
6. I’ve been working on building back up my trust in God. He’s gentle and kind and not offended by my disappointment. 
7. Honesty goes a long way and open dialogue brings connection even when it’s hard. 
8. Getting outside is deeply restorative to the soul. Don’t miss out on the free gift of just being outside! 
9. I can do the hard things that I’ve convinced myself I’d never be able to! 
10. Homeschooling pays off! If you’re thinking about starting go for it and if you’re thinking of quitting don’t! It takes time to see the fruit so give yourself grace and don’t talk yourself out of the full reward!
These simple days are a gift 🎀
